      <p>While the absolute cell count depends on the image analysis threshold which should be adjusted manually and therefore has a factor of subjectivity, the live/dead ratio quantification does not depend on the threshold settings in the range of 15–60 color intensity units (on the 0.255 scale) exhibiting linear function with <italic>R</italic><sup>2</sup> values exceeding 0.9 and regression coefficients of <italic>k</italic> ranging between 0.9 and 1.1 (Tables <xref ref-type="table" rid="pone.0193267.t001">1</xref> and <xref ref-type="table" rid="pone.0193267.t002">2</xref>). This fact allows performing automatic analysis of multiple images with constant settings optimized from the first image in a series.</p>
